<p>Is there a SQL function to return the middle value of three?</p>  <p>For example, assume I have a table with people who have three cars, sorted alphabetically by AutoMaker.</p>  <pre><code>John: Ford John: Honda John: VW </code></pre>  <p>then</p>  <pre><code>MIN(AutoMaker) returns Ford. MAX(AutoMaker) returns VW. </code></pre>  <p>Is there a similar SQL function that will return Honda?</p>  <p>I am working with MS Access and Oracle. </p>  <p>Thank you.</p>